From 936428cf8ae0d692150310a0c4a298bc8e2cb849 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Jun 2025 16:08:31 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Add puncture mask shaping
 helpers for edge and interim types

Introduce helper functions to populate regulatory mask values for punctured
channels in the 6 GHz band. These functions define the offset and dB
reduction (dbr) profiles for different puncture configurations, enabling
accurate shaping of the regulatory mask to meet Out-of-Band Emission (OOBE)
constraints.

Add handle_edge_puncture(), which populates the left and right edge
puncture mask structures for the PUNCTURE_TYPE_EDGE case. Use the provided
edge offsets and the predefined dB reduction profile (pdbm1[]) to define
a symmetric attenuation mask on both sides of the punctured region.

Add handle_interim_20_plus(), which handles both edge and interim shaping
for the PUNCTURE_TYPE_INTERIM_20_PLUS case. Use pdbm1[] for edge shaping
and pdbm2[] for interim shaping. This function ensures smooth transitions
across the punctured and adjacent usable spectrum.

Add handle_interim_20(), which defines a symmetric attenuation profile for
the PUNCTURE_TYPE_INTERIM_20 case using the pdbm3[] profile. This function
shapes the regulatory mask across a 20 MHz interim puncture region.

Update ieee802_11.h with declarations for all three helper functions.

These helpers will be used in subsequent patches to compute regulatory
masks for punctured channels based on bandwidth and puncture bitmap
configuration.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
r80-a-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Introduce-helpers-for-PSD-.patch

Signed-off-by: Vignesh U <uvignesh@qti.qualcomm.com>
